                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Former IPS officer to probe attack
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	New Delhi, April 8: The Centre today appointed E.N. Rammohan, a retired IPS officer, as the one-member inquiry committee to look into the Dantewada ambush that wiped out 76 CRPF personnel on Tuesday.         
	Rammohan has been asked to submit his report in 15 days.         
	He will look into the circumstances leading to the ambush of the platoons of A and G Coys of the 62nd battalion of the CRPF on April 6, 2010, at Tarmetla, PS Jagargunda, district Dantewada, Chhattisgarh, the order issued by the government said.         
	The inquiry has been asked to establish the circumstances preceding and the sequence of events leading to the incident and reconstruct, as far as possible, the events that took place on that day from 5am to noon till the first rescue party reached the place of incident.         
	The panel has been given the responsibility of examining the call records of cellphones used by the CRPF personnel, who were killed or injured in the attack.         
	Rammohan has been asked to analyse and establish the decision/ command structure/ hierarchy and the specific levels which took relevant decisions concerning the AD (Ops) and leading to the incident.                                                                                                                                                           
